sentences: Peter Pontiac (born Peter J.G. Pollmann; 28 April 1951 – 20 January 2015) was a Dutch cartoonist, comics artist and illustrator.
He was the winner of the 1997 Stripschapprijs.
Pontiac died on 20 January 2015, after a lengthy battle with severe liver disease.
He was known for leading a life in the fringe and was addicted to heroin for several years, something he drew autobiographical comics about as well.
2011 - Rhythm, Oog & Blik (Complete collected comics 1969–2011, except Kraut)
2011 - Rhythm, Oog & Blik (Complete collected comics 1969–2011, except Kraut)
1990-1997 - Pontiac Review (a series of 7 books) (Oog & Blik)
1997 - Lost in the Lowlands, self-published, 2nd printing Oog & Blik
1998 - Professor Pi Illustrator's Prize from the city of Amsterdam
2011 - Marten Toonderprijs for his entire oeuvre
